race.comment: DRAMATICUS (4) ran below expectations at Geelong over 1400m, but the Benalla placing as favourite prior over this trip reads well. Maps well and Currie goes on. The McEvoy yard is firing and this is winnable. SUPER SNITCH (8) was good winning the 62 at Warrnambool from a wide draw and can build on that here if he gets the right run. THUNDER POINT (5) is back in grade and better than the form line suggests. Good at the mile and Yendall will likely position forward. Goes in at a price. MUPPET (9) resumes and has jumped out well. Proven fresh and is up to this. Keep well onside. ZAMBORGHINI (2) can improve on recent runs.
